    <item>
      <title>Simple Fullstack NextJS build</title>
      <link>https://wiki.timothylim.is/simple-fullstack-nextjs-build/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 26 Oct 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://wiki.timothylim.is/simple-fullstack-nextjs-build/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;simple-fullstack-nextjs-build&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Simple Fullstack NextJS build&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#simple-fullstack-nextjs-build&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This is what I usually use as a baseline for my projects:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;NextJS (with the app router)&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Served via vercel&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Postgres&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Served via neondb&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Prisma ORM&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;NextAuth, I usually use the twitter login&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://ui.shadcn.com&#34;&gt;shadcn&lt;/a&gt; , plain tailwind or MUI for a front end framework&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Might be helpful to read &lt;a href=&#34;https://wiki.timothylim.is/starting-a-nextjs-project&#34;&gt;how to start a nextjs project&lt;/a&gt; as well.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A simple exercise to get to basic fluency in NextJS could be to create an application with these components. If a user can log in and create something (even if it&amp;rsquo;s just posting some text) it will give you an idea of how a simple fullstack application works.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Starting A NextJS Project</title>
